main event: A detailed UFO sighting report from the Cambria Air Force Station, California on 23 August 1957 involving two objects observed for approximately 30 minutes, exhibiting rapid movement and fading.
interesting points: The observed object(s) were described as round in shape and were of red and orange colors, with no discernible features or tail/exhaust.
Observations were made using ground-visual and ground-electronic means, with the radar operator being considered very reliable.
The objects showed rapid rise and movement, and they were motionless at first before moving laterally and then finally fading away.
Pilots observed the unidentified object(s) during daylight, and clear weather conditions were reported at the time and place of sighting.
Fighter aircraft were vectored toward the objects, and the distance from the initial contact of the objects was estimated at 70 miles.
sighted object: two round-shaped objects of red and orange colors
witnesses: Observations were made by the 775th ACW Squadron, with the radar operator being considered very reliable. Fighter aircraft were also involved in the investigation.
